      "Text": "An update for cpp-httplib is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4",
      "Title": "Summary",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "A C++11 single-file header-only cross platform HTTP/HTTPS library. It\u0026apos;s extremely easy to setup. Just include httplib.h file in your code!\n\nSecurity Fix(es):\n\ncpp-httplib version v0.17.3 through v0.18.3 fails to filter CRLF characters (\"\\r\\n\") when those are prefixed with a null byte. This enables attackers to exploit CRLF injection that could further lead to HTTP Response Splitting, XSS, and more.(CVE-2025-0825)",
      "Title": "Description",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
      "Text": "An update for cpp-httplib is now available for openEuler-22.03-LTS-SP4.\n\nopenEuler Security has rated this update as having a security impact of medium. A Common Vunlnerability Scoring System(CVSS)base score,which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVElink(s) in the References section.",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "General"
    },
